<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Career">Career</span></h2>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Sun_Microsystems">Sun Microsystems</span></h3>

<p>Nadella worked with <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sun_Microsystems" title="Sun Microsystems">Sun
        Microsystems</a> as a member of its technology staff prior to joining Microsoft in 1992.<sup
            id="cite_ref-TOI_01FEB14_2-1" class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-TOI_01FEB14-2">[2]</a></sup></p>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Microsoft">Microsoft</span></h3>

<p>At Microsoft, Nadella has led major projects including the company's move to <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cloud_computing" title="Cloud computing">cloud computing</a> and the
    development of one of the largest cloud infrastructures in the world.<sup id="cite_ref-24" class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-24">[24]</a></sup></p>

<p>Nadella worked as the senior vice-president of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Research_and_Development"
                                                     class="mw-redirect" title="Research and Development">Research and
        Development</a> (R&amp;D) for the Online Services Division and vice-president of the Microsoft Business Division.
    Later, he was made the president of Microsoft's $19 billion Server and Tools Business and led a transformation of
    the company's business and technology culture from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Client_(computing)"
                                                          title="Client (computing)">client services</a> to <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cloud_infrastructure" class="mw-redirect" title="Cloud infrastructure">cloud
        infrastructure</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cloud_services" class="mw-redirect"
                                  title="Cloud services">services</a>. He has been credited for helping bring <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft_SQL_Server" title="Microsoft SQL Server">Microsoft's
        database</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows_Server" title="Windows Server">Windows Server</a>
    and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft_Visual_Studio" title="Microsoft Visual Studio">developer
        tools</a> to its <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows_Azure" class="mw-redirect"
                            title="Windows Azure">Azure</a> cloud.<sup id="cite_ref-Time_19-1" class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-Time-19">[19]</a></sup> The revenue from Cloud
    Services grew to $20.3 billion in June 2013 from $16.6 billion when he took over in 2011.<sup id="cite_ref-25"
                                                                                                  class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-25">[25]</a></sup></p>

<p>Nadella's 2013 base salary was nearly $700,000, for a total compensation, with stock bonuses, of $7.6 million.<sup
            id="cite_ref-26" class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-26">[26]</a></sup></p>

<p>Previous positions held by Nadella include:<sup id="cite_ref-27" class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-27">[27]</a></sup></p>
<ul>
    <li>President of the Server &amp; Tools Division (9 February 2011 – February 2014)</li>
    <li>Senior Vice-President of Research and Development for the Online Services Division (March 2007 – February
        2011)<sup id="cite_ref-28" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-28">[28]</a></sup>
    </li>
    <li>Vice-President of the Business Division</li>
    <li>Corporate Vice-President of Business Solutions and Search &amp; Advertising Platform Group</li>
    <li>Executive Vice-President of Cloud and Enterprise group<sup id="cite_ref-Official_Bio_15-1" class="reference"><a
                    href="#cite_note-Official_Bio-15">[15]</a></sup></li>
</ul>
